N:bmad
D:Route BMAD and BMM phase-based development by choosing project level, identifying the current phase, selecting the next artifact, and advancing through reviewed gates across Claude, Codex, Gemini, and OpenCode.
G:bmad bmm orchestrator workflow planning phase-gate plannotator implementation tea ssd fabric phased-development

U[7]:
  Initialize BMAD workflow for a new or existing project
  Check current phase status and get recommended next action
  Choose the next required artifact: brief, PRD, tech spec, architecture, sprint, or story
  Review phase documents with plannotator before advancing to the next phase
  Route fuzzy-front-end ideation work to bmad-idea instead of forcing BMAD too early
  Add TEA workflows only when risk and quality gates justify them
  Add SSD spec-first artifacts only when the project actually needs them
  Use fabric patterns to tighten BMAD artifacts before review

S[8]{n,action,details}:
  1,Classify,Sort the request into bootstrap phase-status artifact-routing phase-gate or extensions before listing commands
  2,Bootstrap,If BMAD state is missing run /workflow-init to create bmad/config.yaml and docs/bmm-workflow-status.yaml
  3,Route,Use project level plus completed artifacts to recommend /product-brief /prd /tech-spec /architecture /sprint-planning or /dev-story
  4,Defer,Fuzzy-front-end ideation or design-thinking requests go to bmad-idea before structured BMAD delivery
  5,Gate,Run bash scripts/phase-gate-review.sh <doc> before every major phase transition and preserve approve vs revise loop
  6,Extend,Load TEA or SSD only when the artifact or risk profile makes them relevant
  7,Polish,Use fabric patterns only when a BMAD artifact needs improvement before review
  8,Verify,Confirm files and workflow state changed before claiming the phase advanced

R[7]:
  Always choose project level before prescribing the artifact path
  Keep bmad focused on phase routing and artifact progression instead of ideation
  Run phase-gate review before every major phase transition
  Do not reopen unchanged reviewed artifacts without a new revision
  Levels 0-1 usually skip Architecture; Levels 2+ usually require it before implementation
  TEA and SSD are optional extensions unless project risk or artifact requirements make them necessary
  Verify tracked state and output files instead of assuming BMAD advanced
